The Zondo Commission will hear BOSASA related evidence from Sandy Thomas, the Personal Assistant to the former Minister, Nomvula Mokonyane at 10:00 Monday 31 August 2020 at 10:00. JOHANNESBURG - Former Minister Nomvula Mokonyane’s personal assistant is expected to testify at the state capture inquiry. Sandy Thomas will give evidence concerning the relationship between Bosasa and Mokonyane. WATCH: Did Bosasa sponsor Mokonyane's birthday party? The company’s former COO Angelo Agrizzi made damning allegations against the former minister in February 2019. He said she was paid R50,000 per month to influence the Hawks to destroy investigations into Bosasa corruption. Mokonyane has consistently denied the claims.